{{Nihongo|'''Midori'''|美登里}} is a [[human sexuality|sexuality]] writer, speaker, artist, and sex educator based in [[San Francisco]], [[California]], who writes on alternative sexual practices, including [[BDSM]] and [[sexual fetishism]], including [[Bondage (BDSM)|bondage]], [[foot fetishism]], [[Japanese bondage]] and [[shoe fetishism]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.femalefirst.co.uk/relationships/Coco+de+Mer+Launch+Salons-264149.html|title=Coco der Mer Launch Lessons In Love Salons|author=Cara Mason|date=1 November 2012|publisher=|accessdate=21 December 2014}}</ref>
== History == Midori was born in [[Kyoto]], [[Japan]], of [[Japanese people|Japanese]] and [[Germany|German]] parents, and raised with feminist values, while growing up in [[Tokyo]].
Midori moved to the United States as a teenager. She served as a [[United States Army]] Reserves [[United States Army Military Intelligence|Intelligence]] officer while earning her psychology degree from [[University of California, Berkeley]], and spent a few years as a [[sex educator]] with ''[[San Francisco Sex Information]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sfgate.com/style/article/Midori-explains-how-to-have-sex-with-props-3228938.php |work=The San Francisco Chronicle|title=SF Chronicle article}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.comeasyouare.com/toronto-store-information/sex-workshops/our-sex-educators/midori/|title=Midori - Workshop Facilitator Midori at Come As You Are|publisher=Comeasyouare.com|date=|accessdate=2014-12-21|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141221025756/http://www.comeasyouare.com/toronto-store-information/sex-workshops/our-sex-educators/midori/|archivedate=2014-12-21|df=}}</ref>
