{{Infobox university | name = Organization & Method College | native_name = Organization & Method College | native_name_lang = es | image = Logoudoym.gif | image_size = 120px | image_alt = | caption = Seal of O&M College | latin_name = Universidad O&M | other_name = | former_name = | motto = | motto_lang = | mottoeng = | established = {{start date|1966}} | closed = | type = [[Private university|Private]] | parent = | affiliation = | religious_affiliation = | academic_affiliation = | endowment = | budget = | officer_in_charge = | chairman = | chairperson = | chancellor = | president = | vice-president = | superintendent = | provost = | vice_chancellor= | rector = | principal = | dean = | director = | head_label = | head = | academic_staff = | administrative_staff = | students = | undergrad = | postgrad = | doctoral = | other = | city = [[Santo Domingo]] | state = | province = | country = [[Dominican Republic]] | coor = | campus = | language = | free_label = | free = | colors = | athletics = | sports = | athletics_nickname = | mascot = | sporting_affiliations = | website = [http://udoym.edu.do udoym.edu.do] | logo = | footnotes = }}
'''Organization & Method College''' or '''(O&M College)''' is a [[university]] in [[Santo Domingo]] in the [[Dominican Republic]]. It was founded on 1966 by [[José Rafael Abinader]]. It has campus in other cities as well, [[Santiago de los Caballeros]], [[La Romana, La Romana|La Romana]], [[San José de Ocoa]], [[San Felipe de Puerto Plata]], [[Moca, Dominican Republic|Moca]], [[Santo Domingo Este]].
