'''Stella Bruzzi''', [[Fellow of the British Academy|FBA]] (born 28 January 1962) is an Italian-born British scholar of [[Film studies|film]] and [[media studies]]. Since 2006, she has been [[Professor]] of Film and Television Studies at the [[University of Warwick]]. She has previously taught at the [[University of Manchester]] and at [[Royal Holloway]], [[University of London]].<ref name="Who's Who 2017">{{cite web|title=BRUZZI, Prof. Stella, (Mrs Mick Conefrey)|url=http://www.ukwhoswho.com/view/article/oupww/whoswho/U260780|website=Who's Who 2017|publisher=Oxford University Press|accessdate=26 April 2017|date=November 2016}}</ref><ref name="bio Department">{{cite web|title=Professor Stella Bruzzi FBA|url=https://www2.warwick.ac.uk/fac/arts/film/staff/bruzzi/|website=Department of Film and Television Studies|publisher=University of Warwick|accessdate=26 April 2017}}</ref>

==Honours==
In 2013, Bruzzi was elected a [[Fellow of the British Academy]] (FBA), the United Kingdom's [[national academy]] for the humanities and social sciences.<ref name="FBA">{{cite web|title=Professor Stella Bruzzi|url=http://www.britac.ac.uk/users/professor-stella-bruzzi|website=British Academy|accessdate=26 April 2017}}</ref>

