{{portal|Gemology and Jewelry}} {{Infobox person | name = Tanja Manuela Sadow | image = Tanja_Manuela_Sadow.jpg | alt = Tanja M. Sadow, Dean of the [[Jewellery Design and Management International School]] | caption = Tanja M. Sadow, Dean of the [[Jewellery Design and Management International School]] | birth_name = | birth_date = <!-- {{birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} for living people. For people who have died, use {{Birth date|YYYY|MM|DD}}. --> | birth_place = [[England]] | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | nationality = British | other_names = | occupation = Dean, [[Gemologist]], Jeweler, Educator, [[Jewellery designer]], [[Entrepreneur]] | years_active = | known_for = Jewellery Education | notable_works = }}
'''Tanja Manuela Sadow''' is a [[Singapore]] educator and founder of the [[Jewellery Design and Management International School]]
==Early life and education== Sadow studied in Spain, the United Kingdom and attended the [[Gemological Institute of America]] in the United States of America. Her training included various forms of design and she is a graduate Jewellery Gemmologist.
==Career== From 1984 to 1991 Sadow was a resident and extension instructor at the Gemological Institute of America, training jewellers in their Santa Monica campus as well as in 48 US States and conducting GIA's first extension course in Singapore{{citation needed|date=May 2017}}
In 1991 Sadow consulted with the Singapore [[Economic Development Board]],{{citation needed|date=May 2017}} recommending the development of a Singapore-based education facility for the jewellery industry. Later she was commissioned to develop the gemmology curriculum for the newly formed Jewellery Industry Training Centre of Singapore (JITCS). Sadow continued to develop training programmes and deliver gemmology and jewellery training to the Singapore jewellery industry with the JITCS until December 1994.{{citation needed|date=May 2017}}
In 1995 Sadow established a commercial company, JusTanja Pte. Ltd. which she would use to design and distribute jewellery lines in Singapore, Los Angeles and London, stocked by notable department stores such as [[Harrods]] of London. Through this company, Sadow also delivered corporate training to Singapore jewellery firms and raised awareness about gemstones and jewellery with Singapore clubs and communities.{{citation needed|date=May 2017}}
Sadow established the retail brand BeadHub. Between 2000 and 2006, Sadow grew BeadHub from a single member only location to a multi-outlet component and finished jewellery chain in Singapore{{citation needed|date=May 2017}} with locations in [[Wisma Atria]], Emerald Hill Road and Sunshine Plaza as well as a unique DIY jewellery concession within [[Robinson & Co.]] in [[The Centrepoint]]. The BeadHub brand was sold in 2006 following Sadow's desire to pursue the development of a formal training institution.{{citation needed|date=May 2017}}
In 2007 Sadow founded the [[Jewellery Design and Management International School]] in Singapore. She continues to head this organization in the capacity of executive director and dean of the school.
==Activities== Sadow is founder and president of the Guild of Jewellery Professionals and Artisans,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gjpa.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=2&Itemid=2 |title= GJPA Concept & Principles document, written by Tanja Sadow }}</ref> a not-for-profit society registered in Singapore, and an executive committee member of the Singapore Jewellers Association,<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.sja.org.sg/about-us/executive-members|title= Singapore Jeweller's Association Executive Committee Members|deadurl= yes|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20140708151408/http://www.sja.org.sg/about-us/executive-members|archivedate= 2014-07-08|df= }}</ref> a not-for-profit association registered in Singapore.
Sadow regularly delivers public talks and workshops both in Singapore<ref>{{cite web|url= https://blog.science.edu.sg/2013/01/10/discover-the-science-of-gems-with-tanja-sadow-part-ii/ |title= Discover the Science of Gems event at Singapore Science Centre }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://asiapacificnewswire.com/singapore-jewellery-gem-fair-2016-host-design-award-bespoke-fashion-show-10-discounts-partnership-mastercard/|title=Tanja Sadow delivers talks at workshops at Singapore Jewellery & Gem Fair' }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sije.com.sg/contents/file/SIJE%202015%20Post%20Event%20Sheet.pdf |title=Tanja Sadow delivering free stage talks at Singapore International Jewellery Expo }}</ref> and the Asia-Pacific region<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.manilatimes.net/why-tiffany-co-is-a-precious-symbol-of-love/220749/ |title=Tanja Sadow educating Tiffany & Co. customers and member of the general public in Manila, Philippines }}</ref> to promote jewellery appreciation and interest in the jewellery industry. She also works with international brands to provide educational content to support their outreach activities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://prestigeonline.com/sg/Events/Prestige-Events/Tiffany-Co.-x-Prestige/Tanja-Sadow |title= Tanja Sadow delivers talk for Tiffany & Co. on coloured gemstones }}</ref> Sadow also provides authoritative viewpoints for press articles in Singapore and around the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/newspapers/Digitised/Page/straitstimes20001215-1.1.123 |title= GLAMORISING THE CRAFTS [ARTICLE + ILLUSTRATION] The Straits Times, 15 December 2000, Page 11 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/newspapers/Digitised/Page/biztimes20011127-1.1.24 |title= Trendsetters [ARTICLE + ILLUSTRATION] The Business Times, 27 November 2001, Page 24 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/newspapers/Digitised/Page/straitstimes20030710-1.1.46 |title= ROCKS OF NEW AGE [ARTICLE + ILLUSTRATION] The Straits Times, 10 July 2003, Page 8 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/newspapers/Digitised/Page/biztimes20051125-1.1.43 |title= Well treated gems [ARTICLE + ILLUSTRATION] The Business Times, 25 November 2005, Page 44 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/newspapers/Digitised/Page/biztimes20051125-1.1.48 |title= Crystal ball-gazing with jewellers [ARTICLE] The Business Times, 25 November 2005, Page 49 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/newspapers/Digitised/Page/straitstimes20090731-1.1.122 |title= METAL CRAFTSMEN [ARTICLE + ILLUSTRATION] The Straits Times, 31 July 2009, Page 122 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://omanobserver.om/jewellery-rock-star-2017-tourmaline/ |title=The Jewellery rock-star of 2017 could be tourmaline [Article] Oman Observer, 8 April 2017}}</ref>
Sadow has been a judge at local and international jewellery design competitions, including the [[Singapore Jewellery Design Award]]<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.sjda.sg/competitions/jewellery-design-tips|title= Tanja Sadow provides design tips to SJDA participants}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url= http://luxesocietyasia.com/style/singapore-jewelry-and-gem-fair-2016-shine-brighter-than-the-stars/ |title= Tanja Sadow involved in 2016 Singapore Jewellery & Gem Fair}}</ref>
